This option is used to set the encoding for reject message when setting up the PLC cofigurations.
The encoding value specified in this option is used to set the response encoding throught the HttpServletResponse.setCharacterEncoding("encoding") API.

Alternatively, if the encoding is broken by the browser and the environment you are using, then you can use HTML tags to set the message.

Here is an example using HTML tags.

     <html>
       <head>
         <meta charset = "utf-8" />
         <meta http-equiv = "Content-Type" content = "text / html; charset = utf-8" />
       </ head>
       <body> Message </ body>
     </ html>

---

* Default : None
* Type : String
* Sample Value

    UTF-8
    
* Restart : Not Required
* Supported Version : 5.3.1.2